      "description": "The Google design system is a 'dark mode first' experience with a substantial canvas of deep charcoal and highly subtle surface differentiation. Interaction elements are clearly defined through achromatic outlines and fills, while a carefully restrained use of vibrant, multi-hued gradients and blue accents provides bursts of visual interest for key actions and branding. Typography is generally clean and monochromatic, appearing as crisp white against dark surfaces, relying on weight and size for hierarchy. The overall feel is one of understated functionality and quiet efficiency.",
